Let's get into scripture

We are moving through sermon on the mount, arguably the most powerful and famous sermon ever given

It was given by Jesus in front of thousands of people and the account we're reading was written by Matthew

Matthew is one of the 4 gospels in the new testament of the bible

Matthew was an outcast jew who abandoned his life as a tax collector for rome to become one of Jesus' closest students known as apostles

The 12 apostles spent time with Jesus and served as eyewitnesses to his teachings and interactions over the course of his ministry

Matthews account of sermon on the mount is the most detailed account. It spans 111 verses, around 2400 words and takes around 15 minutes to read end to end 


Up to this point in sermon on the mount, we've covered Kingdom character with the beatitudes where Jesus proclaims blessings on those who are

Poor in spirit, those who mourn, those who are mek, those who hunger for righteousness, those who are merciful, those who are pure in heart

Those who are peacemakers, those who are persecuted for righteousness sake and blessings to those who are persecuted falsely on Jesus' account


After Kingdom character came Kingdom identity - Christians being the salt of the earth that preserve goodness and the light that shines through darkness

After identity comes the law. Kingdom rules that govern how we behave towards God and one another

After the law, Jesus talks about Kingdom behaviours starting with anger and lust 

Jesus then speaks about divorce and oaths which we covered in our last service

That brings us to verse 38 where Jesus talks about retaliation

